16 WHEREAS, police chiefs and heads of law enforcement agencies of Georgia support the
17 continuous elevation of standards and training of law enforcement managers and have been
18 instrumental in increasing the public's awareness of methods for avoiding being victims of
19 crime; and
20 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the police chiefs and heads of law
21 enforcement agencies of Georgia be recognized for their many personal sacrifices as well as
22 their outstanding and courageous contributions to the citizens of this state.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
24 recognize March 6, 2025, as Police Chiefs and Heads of Law Enforcement Agencies Day at
25 the state capitol and commend each police chief and head of a law enforcement agency in
26 this state for his or her outstanding commitment to the people of this state.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to Scott Gray,
29 President of the Georgia Association of Chiefs of Police, and A. A. Butch Ayers, Executive
30 Director of the Georgia Association of Chiefs of Police.
